  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Study tour on social control mechanisms for crop substitution</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Colombian farmer organisations of coca growers will acquire and apply practical knowledge of successful experiences in Bolivia regarding substitution, social control and alternative uses of coca. Also, the Government representative who will participate in the study tour will bring back valuable experiences and perspectives from Bolivia and apply some of the lessons learned in Colombia. Finally, the project will contribute to increase trust and mutual understanding between ANZORC and the Government of Colombia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Visit to public institutions in La Paz, Bolivia; visit to coca syndicates in La Paz, Bolivia; field visit to Los Yungas and Chapara, Bolivia; document and systematise lessons learned from the study tour; share the lessons learned: produce and share a synthesis document on the documentation and systematization, produce and share a video as well as a photo gallery, write and share a news article, share the experience at five regional forums.</narrative>
  </description>
